{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CurMyyw92xWhVQ6kQsHm36","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Let me outline my proposed changes before writing the plan.\n\n**Failure 1 (Baked Eggs):** The continuation protection only removes the PREFIX single (`Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce`) but not the SUFFIX single (`& Coriander`). The suffix survives, triggers \"shorter wins\" dedup, and kills the join. Fix: extend the `survivingJoins` block to also remove suffix fragments that start with a continuation character.\n\n**Failure 2 (Saffron Wheat Buns):** This is primarily an evaluation mismatch — the OCR text has `/` but the filename (expected title) has `:` because `/` is illegal in filenames. The algorithm may already be returning the correct text. Fix: normalize `/` ↔ `:` in the `titles_match` function. Secondary: make the OCR truncation penalty a hard disqualification instead of a fragile -0.15."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3445,"cache_read_input_tokens":64680,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3445},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5981ad23-b316-4039-b950-1d2ae18ba9be","uuid":"2b33a522-4d2c-4394-bb20-2c646a144869"}
